	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=27944><span id= >sgbishop</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Who has more downtime (AKA sitting on your butt), a Bard or a Necro?&nbsp;&nbsp;And please explain.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>3 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f104853414921575>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=104853414921575>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104853414921575>RE: Downtime</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104853414921575#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Mar 24th 3:04 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=197822><span id= >beowulfus</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>At the time of this writing, I have a 51 bard and a 48 necro, each soloed to this point.&nbsp;&nbsp;Properly managed, neither has very much in the way of downtime.  I remember having a hard time with both until I finally made it into the mid-levels.  And this discussion may be inappropriate for the levels below 20, because I think I may have blocked all of that part of play.<br><br>Solo bards are, however, dead a lot until they get Angstlich's Screech, which is a fear effect that surrounds the bards person.  Once they get that, they slow with Selo's Consonant Chain and fear with the Screech and thump the target in the back.  Pretty easy, and if you mess up, it won't take TOO long to scrape yourself back up. At the beginning, bards have reduced downtime because they can sing themselves healthy, and, of course, they have shockingly few HP to regen (bards don't use mana except in rare circumstances or to charm. Once the bard becomes wealthy enough to wear the Singing Steel breastplate, he is wearing a clickable 100 point heal, and this reduces downtime even more.<br><br>Bards are a blast when you're in the mood for them, and nothing beats them for travel, unless you're a plane-jumper.<br><br>Now, necromancers have to sit down occasionally, but not all that much.  They can accelerate their mana regen rate by converting HP to mana.  This sound bad until you remember that their lowest resist damage spell is a life tap, so there is nothing easier than to heal right back up.  This assumes, of course, that you are not getting hit.  Do not believe the nonsense about tanking necros; that is NOT what they do.  They wear stamina gear to allow them to lich themselves longer and more safely.  Also, a necromancer is not an efficient dealer of direct damage by way of spells; they can do it but at an enormous mana cost to do pathetically small damage for the level.  They do damage over time.  The typical becromantic pattern is slow, pet, scare, dot, dot, med, giggle while pet chases target, jump up and refear if it wears off, heal pet if necessary, and, if a lil hungry, suck a lil life outta the poor victim.  If you don't blow mana by using in inefficiently, you can take out half a dozen targets before you have to med.<br><br>As to purchased buffs, by the way, I recommend Aegolism over KEI for a necromancer.  But then mine is a dark elf, and I like to keep her liching, pacting, call it what you will, because I like the way it makes her giggle when she casts.  It would be interesting to know what an Iksar necromancer's view are on this subject.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
