	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=104480917167413>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104480917167413>44-51 in one spot!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104480917167413#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Feb 9th 12:16 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=203298><span id=Scholar>Dread Lord Boneklaw</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>73 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Welcome fellow dark ones.I wish to lay out for you a great way to fly from 44 to 51 without every changing your camp area.You could do this under 44 but I would not recommend it.You will need Dead Man Floating constantly up is why.<br><br>Ok get yourselves to Lake of Ill Omen.The targets are Bloodgills(under water blue goblins that can come up on land).In the middle of the lake is one of the best kept secrets for leveling in my opinion.There under water is the sunken temple.Its a Large Dome shapped temple that has a flat ledge all the way around it.The ledge is squared off and has 4 corners.Each corner has pillars that stretch up above the water line.From the shore you can see the corners of the temple.<br><br>One corner has a platform that you can stand on and its right at water level so tech. the platform is under water but while on it your out of water.Go to the plateform.You can bind here (if you want) and I always make my pet here.(tracking can get wild in Loio and I have often lost my pet while running from cabilis.)<br><br>All your fighting is under water so make sure you freshen up your DMF often in your down&nbsp;&nbsp;times.Having DMF fade during a fight will get you killed.<br><br>Grab the pet, buff the pet, buff yourself and dive! Dont go straight down two bloodgills are directly below you on the platform. Instead swim out a bit and dive down to see the flat ledge.I always kept the rounded dome to my right and rotated the four corners in a clockwise manner.<br><br>There are two at every corner and as soon as you attack one they both come.This is the way to handle these mobs.Target and cast root on the nearest BG(bloodgill-BG from here out)As soon as you do the farthest one charges.You have a few seconds to target it and send the pet.As soon as the pet engages the BG,cast darkness.Then Fear the BG.Quickly retarget the rooted BG and command pet to attack it.Then Darkness the BG and Dot(I used chilling embrace)Lastly fear the BG.This way if root breaks early (rare) your not alone with a very upset BG that will beat your brains out.It was almost perfect that the pet finished the first BG as root broke on the second one.Since you already told pet attack here comes your pet screaming into action right as the BG turns to run.Since you dotted him already your pet can work quickly to finish him before your snare or fear fade.I suggest staying in lich the whole time and tapping your new blue friends as needed.Proper mob managment here is crucial but you are the master of soloing and you can handle it.I only died once from 44-51 and I drowned in the middle of a fight when DMF wore off ..Hence the warning to refresh it.<br><br>Closing thoughts....For those of you who know this area your gonna say what about the 5 BG at the base of the temple on the west side.Yes there are 5 more including the Dreadful Bloodgill Maurader.So here is where PART 2 comes in.Once you hit 49 your new pet is a killing machine.He will rip through the BG's like nothing.You will then find on the top rotation of corners no need to dot anymore just keep doing what you have been but save your mana.He kills so quickly you dont need to.Just lifetap for help while in lich.You will find your always ahead of the spawn so now its time to add some to your routine.<br><br>Once 49 keep your rotation up but this time when you face west instead of going around the circle go straight at the corner and dive down.Careful here til you learn where these guys spawn.One will be away from the temple at the base of a broken piller.DO not fear him.Pet is a tank now just snare him and /pet attack.From this pillar go straight north just a little ways and you see another single.Repeat here like the first.Now come back about half way between those two pillars and head like your going to the temple.Go slow til you see the double spawn on each side of the temple door.The problem is just inside that door is a Bloodgill Marauder.If you attack any of these guys you get all 3.I highly suggest you have Paralyzing earth up.Park pet (/pet guard here).Slowly creep in til you can get a target on the marauder.He is just inside the door and hard to see as it is shaded in there.Cast PE on  him (can last up to 3 min ...and your gonna need all time you can get).When you do its 99% likely you have two BG charging you. Run to pet. Pet will take on both.While he is tough he isnt this tough.Cast Darkness/fear on one asap.Repeat for the other.Target the first one and dot it with anything you want to.Now quickly get back to the maurder.Snare him then fear him right away.If PE Still hasnt broke Dot him.You got it from here.Pet finishes other two you then finish the marauder.He is a 4 hour or so spawn get rid of him and your back to your pulling two strategy that you use up top.go back up top and start your rotation around again.When you get back to the west side.Dive again as it is almost perfect timing for mobs to start poping again.<br><br>BG turned mixed LtBlue and Dk blue at 51 but mostly LtBlue.Good luck I know this was wordy BUT you now have NO Excuses as I have just layed out how I went from 44-51 and you dont have to do anything but read and go do it.<br><br>PLEASE RATE THIS POST<br>If you try this and are happy you read about it please come back and post to let me know.Good luck Dark ones!!!<br><br> </p>&nbsp;<br>Boneklaw Von`Torment<br>Sullon Zek</td></td></tr>
