	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Feb 8th 7:07 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=203298><span id=Scholar>Dread Lord Boneklaw</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>73 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>First of all I am not sure how much money you have to spend.So I am making suggestions based on a limited budjet.In this way I hope to lay down some practical advise for anyone in your same shoes but maybe without a higher char to help with money etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>No doubt you will recieve as many different answers on this as are people playing the game.That said I will say from my personal exp,I would invest in a good 1hb.Staff of Writhing is perfect for you.Procs later on too.They are cheap as well.(forget pierce,your epic is 1hb train it..use it)<br><br>You didn't list your race.Thats important as it tells me some idea of your starting intel.However at level 8 your still needing to get in and mix it up a bit with the mobs.So a SMALL amount of attention should be payed to some cheap armor.I would suggest a minimal amount be spent on a robe with some intel on it.Robe of the oracle is currently cheap as are Flowing black robes(awsome look btw)You may even pick up a Robe of enshourdment for free or very cheap.(I gave mine away to a lower necro)As you can, gather intel items ...rings, bracers, earrings etc, anything with intel on it.Buy cheap items, save, upgrade sell off what you just upgraded off of.<br><br>Lastly get yourself to Field of bone. You can hunt the  mobs in the pit area. Have pet guard against the wall and pull to the wall from the many mobs in the pit.The walls are safe spots to fear kite etc. The ramps are always safe place to med and heal also.<br><br>At level 10 go on up to kurns tower(same zone near the end of pit) and you can level just inside the zone (dungeon XP bonus here too WOOT). DONT FEAR HERE. Time to melee oh great necro.Use the Two on one theory, you and your pet.Snare always to pull. Send pet as the mob gets very close.Throw a dot and head in to fight.Dont go mana crazy on these mobs.Save mana and increase your pull rate.At first level just inside the zone.If it breaks bad your steps away from safety.This whole zone is 90%undead skellies.This will take you to level 15.<br><br>Next go outside of kurns.At the back of kurns at where the ramp begins make a pet and /pet guard here.Up against the wall near the ramp is fine.Go pull Hearsting Scorpions to the wall.You can fear kite here if you get the mob near the wall before you fear it.Stay here til level 20.<br><br>One thing to consider if you have PoP bind in PoK til you get 16 (then you get bind).If you dont have PoP then have someone bind you in Keasora area,its near where you will be fighting ...and FOB is gonna be your home for a while.I know you asked what to do at 8 but I just laid out how to get to 20 for you.<br><br>Good luck young necro! It's one of the most challenging yet most rewarding classes to play.And at 49+...well its just insane how much fun I started having ;-) <br><br>Please rate this post<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Feb  9 11:57:14 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Boneklaw Von`Torment<br>Sullon Zek</td></td></tr>
