	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=14&mid=104526095530771>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104526095530771>RE: noob help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104526095530771#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Feb 14th 5:47 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120740><span id=Scholar>ayere</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>27 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you are looking for equipment, stat's to enhance for necromancers go in this order:<br><br>1) HP's<br>2) Mana<br>3) Int<br>4) Stamina<br>5) Resists<br><br>If you focus on this priority, you will end up with the right mix in the long run. Rule of thumb is that any +INT item you equip should also have +HP on it (+Mana too if posssible). This way, since it is fairly easy to increase INT, your HP's and Mana pool should end up fairly well balanced. You'll understand why when you get into using the Lich/Bond of Death line of spells for mana regen.&nbsp;&nbsp;I learned this at a later point in my necromancer's life; sometimes I wish I could roll back the clock and put half my bonus points into STA and half into INT (maybe all into STA since it's so easy to raise INT these days). <br><br>Personally, I stopped meleeing all together once I got my level 8 pet or so, and I regret it. It's much harder to build up defense skills when mob's double for 250-300 (owch). Take the time to step in and take a beating for your pet once in a while. You can easily tap the health back, and your pet doesn't take as much of a beating. Also, I wish I'd have worked up my 2hb (yes, the epic is 1hb, but you'll never hit anything with it - except with the clicky effect which is a spell anyway). However, I do use my OT hammer (2hb) which proc's a gate to OT - very handy if you are bound near your hunting grounds and want to get to PoK/Nexus or just to vendors and a bank quickly.<br><br>As for where to hunt, I basically looked at what other people were grouping to hunt at my level and went out and solo'ed the same things. I still do this, actually. There are some nice static spawns, but at your level I think I was hunting wandering random stuff in WC. Once you get FD, you can single pull about anything other groups are hunting.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br><br>Syre D'Fleshh<br>57 Defiler, Inny</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
