	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Feb 5th 3:26 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139782><span id=Sage>vikeshta</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you have Shadows of Luclin, then this may work for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;Merchantbot.  Find stuff that you can kill and sell it.  You'd be surprised at what you can accomplish:<br><br>Up until your teens, there are many places where you can hunt undead for bonechips, various animals for pelts and spiders for their silks.  Your target audience for sales are high-level characters and tradeskillers.<br><br>High-level necromancers (and to a lesser extent, shadowknights), have better things to do than chase around mobs that were green to them 40 - 50 levels ago for bonechips.  But they need them.  Gather them and collect stacks and stacks of 'em.  On The Nameless server, bonechips sell anywhere from 5gp to 1pp per bonechip -- that's 10pp to 20pp per stack.  And people do buy them.  Why?  Because 20pp is pocket change to a level 50+ character.<br><br>Silks and pelts are another great source of money, if you hunt the right creatures.  East Karana is a great spot to farm spiders and lions.  Save all the spider and spiderling silk you find, as well as any 'quality' pelts. (Low, Medium, High.)  Tradeskillers need these pelts for a variety of skills and items, and they sell well.  Over one weekend, my merchantbot made well over 1000pp selling stacks of various quality pelts.  That'll buy all your necro spells for some time!<br><br>One last item are zombie skins, which come off a variety of other undead all over Norrath and Luclin.  While they sell a little slower, they can sell in the Bazaar as well.  Again, tradeskillers can use them.  My personal best was to sell 5 stacks of zombie skins for 100pp per stack.   Sure it took a while, but that's the beauty of the Bazaar -- you may just get someone who wants it RIGHT NOW and if you're there, you've got a sale.<br><br>So to recap, leave a merchant logged in while you're at work or sleeping with things that tradeskillers and high level characters want.  Many of these are easy hunting, and GIVE XP to boot. Cash and exp -- what more can you want?<br><br>Vikeshta D'cire<br>Citizen of the <a href=HTTP://www.foolsrepublic.com target=_new>Fools Republic</a><br>The Nameless<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  5 04:09:37 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
