	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=139782><span id=Sage>vikeshta</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Although this can't help you, Sharrd, I thought I'd share this for players who have Planes of Power and Luclin.&nbsp;&nbsp;(BTW, you may want to consider getting POP -- the portstones alone are worth the price, IMO.)<br><br>One nice mid-level item is a <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=16394 target=_new>Fine Cut, Diamond Inlaid Mask</a>.  Stats are:<br><br>Fine Cut, Diamond Inlaid Mask<br>LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP<br>AC: +3 Sta: +3 Wis: +3 Int: +3 Magic Resist: +3 HP: +10 Mana: +10<br>Weight: 0.6<br>Classes: All Classes<br>Races: All Races<br>Inventory Slot: Face<br>Focus Effect: Spell Haste II<br><br>This is the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2203 target=_new>Magic Pool quest</a> on the Plane of Knowledge.  The only item you need to get is some Sarnak Blood, which you can easily kill at 37, or buy off a vendor for a little over 1pp. (I see them all the time on vendors.)  The quest is mostly running around, culminating with a run through Droga to find someone.  Sure, it's scary, but if you don't have anything anyways, dying shouldn't be a problem. :)  Great item if you've the stomach, though.<br><br>If you're ready to put in a little more work, another decent mid-level item is the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2203 target=_new>Fine Antique Ring</a>:<br><br>Fine Antique Ring<br>LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM NO DROP<br>AC: +3 HP: +30 Mana: +20<br>Weight: 0.1<br>Classes: All Classes<br>Races: All Races<br>Inventory Slot: Finger<br>Focus Effect: Mana Preservation II<br><br>This comes from <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2193 target=_new>Holly Longtail's Replacement Parts quest</a>, also on the Plane of Knowledge.  You need to collect 4 items from her, many of which you can vendordive for, or just go out and kill.  Follow up on the quest link, and you'll see what you need. <br><br>Here's a quest that involves a lot of running around, but gives you plat and experience when you're done.  <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2200 target=_new>Trep's Shopping List quest</a> requires about 30pp to do, but gives about 60pp when you're done, making it a +30 plat gain (and xp) when you're finished.  You end up running around every expansion to do it, though.<br><br>Here are a few more quests that give mid-level items. (All with Focus Effects, I might add, just like the ones above!)<br><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2190 target=_new>Renni's Rock Collection</a><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2198 target=_new>Randi's Floral Specimins</a><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2199 target=_new>Merri's Artifact Collection</a><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2191 target=_new>Drelyn's Gem Collection</a><br><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2195 target=_new>Alexis' Book Collection</a><br><br>Good luck with your gearing up!<br><br>Vikeshta D'cire<br>Citizen of the <a href=HTTP://www.foolsrepublic.com target=_new>Fools Republic</a><br>The Nameless<br><br>Edit: Fixed links<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  5 04:10:00 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
