	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=199801><span id= >Belthazor</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hello Xaniroka,<br><br>I too hunted around the pit.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once I was level 10 I have moved to some huge, undead filled tower. I can't remember the name, but it is a large tower that can be easily found in the middle of the field of bones-- just follow the circumference of the pit and you'll run right by it. Lvl up to 10 at the pit, then go.  Using multiple ward undead spells I can take down low red skeletons.  Come armed with this spell, as well as invisibility to undead, dark pact, and clinging darkness.  Stay by the tower entrance, and fight one at a time .  They team up pretty often and you'll be running to zone a lot.  Your pet is weak in comparison to these enemies (I guess until 12), so cast ward undead as fast as possible-- and expect many fizzles because it's the first evocation spell necros get.  This also means you'll be recovering mana a lot.  This is, IMO, the best place to hunt for a necro at your level-- as long as you fight smart, you'll gain many levels very quickly.<br><br>-Belthazor</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
